dels, Schaffner also examines the ways that self-improvement practices provide powerful barometers of the values, anxieties, and aspirations that preoccupy us at particular moments in time and expose basic assumptions about our purpose and nature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aConduct of life. 0aSelf-actualization (Psychology). 0aSelf-help techniques. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262391423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262391/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles